 department as special assistant to the president and senior director for russia ukraine and eurasia at the national security council and us ambassador to ukraine most recently he was vice president and director of foreign policy studies at the brookings institution simpleviewer requires macromedia flash get macromedia flash if you have flash installed click to view gallery large gallery photos from pascual lecture october 20 2010 payne distinguished lecture series 2010 mexico at a crossroads october 20 2010 lecture series carlos pascual 80 download from the event video video transcript streaming flash video audio audio transcript streaming mp3 pdf+ speech modified october 2010 pdf pascual_stanford_speech pdf 203.9 kb pdf+ presentation modified october 2010 pdf mexico_at_a_crossroads pdf 6.5 mb search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest former us ambassador to japan discusses the okinawa base issue shorenstein aparc japan studies program in the news asahi shimbun on december 12 2011 sprie's china 2.0 conference highlights challenges facing online social media in china shorenstein aparc sprie in the news the wall street journal on october 20 2010 ambassador susan rice fight poverty and fundamental inequalities video+ june 14 2010 news carlos pascual 80 named us ambassador to mexico joins president obama in guadalajara august 11 2009 in the news stanford alumni discuss entrepreneurial challenges in china march 1 2007 shorenstein aparc sprie news cancelled honorable marcello pera's address on challenges facing europe and the united states january 25 2006 news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
